5:
Nicely done, you two! Looks like it
was a cinch after all!
8:
Thanks to your protection, Alk! Look
at me—not a single scratch!
11:
It was you who noticed the enemies
behind us in time, Metis.
14:
I think we can all agree that we
make a pretty good team!
17:
We're down in the Midways today,
right? It's supposed to be pretty
deep, actually... Are you sure this is
okay?
22:
As long as you stay on your toes,
we'll be as fine as fine can be! Trust
me—I know EXACTLY where our limits
lie.
24:
I know all your strengths, Alk. Of
course, that also includes all of your
weaknesses as well. You'll be fine as
long as you manage to stay
focused!
28: I didn't ask about all that!
31:
Aww, are you blushing? Oh, I could
just gobble you up!
35:
A-anyway! Do you think the
adventurers lost in the Kaleidoscope
have anything to do with the
tremors?
41:
There's still much unknown about
the Kaleidoscope tremors, so be
careful. If the ground falls out from
beneath you—
52:
Oh. Well, this is unfortunate.
Someone had better call a medic...
but not for me!
58: Oof... That was quite a fall.
61:
Just me, huh? Okay... Just stay calm
and look for a way up.
71:
Thanks. I feel a lot better—now that
you're here.
74: Stay back, Stella! I'll handle this.
82:
Woo, way to be a hero, Alk! You've
even got me a little flustered with
that one!
85:
But if you think I'd let someone take
the spotlight from me that easily,
think again!
88:
We really ought to make it out of
here before dinner—wouldn't want
to miss our reservation, right?
96: I'm ready to take 'em all on!
97:
But of course, your help would be
greatly appreciated.
102: Of course. Let's wrap this up already!
110:
You still wield the relic, I see. Didn't
expect to see me again, did you?
112:
Both you and Hayate... cursed
adventurers who would reveal these
secrets to the world...
113:
Your bow. That pride of yours . You
are not worthy...
115:
Did you not get the memo? Sorry,
but Metis Phronesis only deserves
the best of the best!
120:
You think I'd appear without having
made preparations to deal with a
monster like you?
124:
O darkness that sleeps within the
shadows... Unholy tomb of night,
grant this sleepless vessel a dream
eternal.
132: Like I said... You are unworthy.
134:
O darkness that sleeps within the
shadows... Umbral palace, show us
humility!
140:
Metis Phronesis. This empty stage, a
world without viewers—your
greatest fear.
142:
You are alone, Metis. Despite your
cutesie and charming persona that
you try ever so hard to put on.
143:
But one day, you will be forgotten.
And all who have followed you will
one day find a new dream.
144:
That is the way of this world. That is
your fate, Metis.
146:
You cannot turn back the hands of
time. Which is why, at this perfect
moment, I—
150:
Sorry not sorry, but could you wrap it
up?
153:
I've got a dinner reservation to catch
after this, you know? Rude.
158: Tch... Make light of me, will you?
162:
No duh, idiot. But that's fine. As long
as there's someone out there who
dreams of me...
163:
That'll be more than enough
motivation for me to take on the
world.
166:
I'll continue to be the best me I can
be in order to stand among them!
169:
You understand not what you speak,
you—
172:
Oh yeah? That's rich, coming from
some loner in the shadows.
174:
It looks to me like you need a bit of a
shock to wake up! Come on, let's
dance!
180:
Of course it is! I am the one and
only...
182:
Metis Phronesis! The most
splendorous adventurer to ever set
foot in the Kaleidoscope!
184:
So you'd better tuck tail and run if
you know what's best for you, nerd.
188:
I stand no chance against a
monster...
189:
But do not forget this, Celestial Blitz.
The abyss shall swallow all
eventually.
196:
Silly man, fate isn't predetermined.
It's something you make for yourself!
198:
And I'll always believe in the one
that shines most in my life—me!
209:
That's my line, Alk. I'm glad you two
look unharmed.
216:
It looks like it! And all thanks to you
two, of course.
218:
...And all the other wonderfully brave
warriors daring to dive deep into the
Kaleidoscope! With our combined
efforts, nothing can stop us!
225:
Yeah... I wonder what happened to
her?
228:
Quit your dawdling and get on, you
two! We've got a reservation to
catch!
